==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Celtium
<hw>Cel"ti*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>The first proposed name for a supposed new
element of the rare-earth group, accompanying lutecium and scandium in
the gadolinite earths. It is now considered identical to
<er>Lutetium</er>. The proposed symbol was <it>Ct</it> (no period), but
this name and symbol are no longer used.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>celtuce</ent>⟦br⟧
